  The mail reader help on understanding the mail header.

  The command 'from' will list the headers of the messages in your mailbox.
  The following example will explain what all columns mean. Use 'from new'
  to list only those messages you have not read before.

   7: Mercade    Subj: New mail system                 *R* 27 Sep 30

  Number  : 7            (You are requested to remove/archive mail regularly!)
  Author  : Mercade
  Reply   : "Subj:" original mail    "Re:" reply to a mail
  Subject : New mail system
  Status  : *R* message is read      *D* message is marked for deletion
  Length  : 27 lines     (So you can choose to use more if you need to)
  Arrival : Sep 30

